    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.

    @FunctionalInterface
public interface ThrowingBooleanToByteFunction1
extends AbstractThrowingBooleanToByteFunction1<AbstractThrowingBooleanToByteFunction1.Handler>
    Represents a function that accepts a boolean-valued argument and produces a byte-valued result or throws a throwable. This is the one-arity specialization of ThrowingToByteFunctionN. This is the boolean-consuming primitive specialization of ThrowingToByteFunction1. This is the byte-producing primitive specialization of ThrowingBooleanFunction1. This is the throwing variation of BooleanToByteFunction1.

    This is a functional interface whose functional method is AbstractThrowingBooleanToByteFunction1.applyAsByte(boolean).

    Since:
    1.0.0
    See Also:
    ThrowingBooleanFunction1, ThrowingToByteFunction1, ThrowingToByteFunctionN, BooleanToByteFunction1
